</p></sec></app></app-group><glossary><title>Abbreviations</title><def-list><def-item><term>AIDS</term><def><p>Acquired immunodeficiency syndrome</p></def></def-item><def-item><term>CARL</term><def><p>Critical Appraisal Resource Library</p></def></def-item><def-item><term>HIV</term><def><p>Human immunodeficiency virus</p></def></def-item><def-item><term>IHC</term><def><p>Informed Healthcare Choices</p></def></def-item><def-item><term>P. 5</term><def><p>Primary five</p></def></def-item><def-item><term>REC</term><def><p>Research and Ethics Committee</p></def></def-item><def-item><term>SOMREC</term><def><p>School of Medicine Research and Ethics Committee</p></def></def-item><def-item><term>UNCST</term><def><p>Uganda National Council for Science and Technology</p></def></def-item><def-item><term>WHO</term><def><p>World Health Organisation</p></def></def-item></def-list></glossary><ack><title>Acknowledgements</title><p>We thank Jan Odgaard-Jensen for help planning the statistical analyses, and all of the many parents, journalists, teachers, and children who helped with the development of the IHC podcast. We would also like to thank the producers and the musicians who helped with the production of IHC theme song and the podcast. Lastly, but not least, we also acknowledge the support extended to us by the research assistants and the members of the National and International Advisory Panels of the IHC project.</p><sec id="FPar1"><title>Funding</title><p>The trial has been funded by the Norwegian Research Council, Project number 220603/H10. The funding body has had no role in the design of the study or in writing reports.</p></sec><sec id="FPar2"><title>Availability of data and materials</title><p>The datasets generated during the study and used in the analyses will be available from the corresponding author on reasonable request.</p></sec><sec id="FPar3"><title>Authors&#x02019; contributions</title><p>DS participated in the design of the study, the design of the study inter