he results. The principal investigators are responsible for managing data collection. All of the investigators have reviewed the protocol, provided input, and agreed on this version of the manuscript.</p></sec><sec id="FPar4"><title>Competing interests</title><p>The authors declare that they have no competing interests.</p></sec><sec id="FPar5"><title>Consent for publication</title><p>Not applicable.</p></sec><sec id="FPar6"><title>Ethics approval and consent to participate</title><p>This study has obtained ethics approval from the Uganda National Council for Science and Technology (UNCST) and the School of Medicine Research and Ethics Committee (SOMREC) at Makerere University College of Health Sciences (REC number 2013&#x02013;105). Only participants who have provided informed consent (Additional files <xref rid="MOESM1" ref-type="media">1</xref> and <xref rid="MOESM2" ref-type="media">2</xref>) will be included in the study. Participants will not be identified by their personal details and all information will be kept confidential.</p></sec><sec id="FPar7"><title>Trial management</title><p>The trial is registered in the Pan African Clinical Trial Registry [<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR43">43</xref>]. Dr. Daniel Semakula is the principal investigator of the trial, assisted by coinvestigator Allen Nsangi. They will be responsible for the practical implementation of the study and its day-to-day management. They will ensure that staff adhere to the protocol and the guidelines for research involving human participants. Dr. Andrew David Oxman, Dr. Atle Fretheim, the IHC Team at the Norwegian Institute of Public Health, and Prof. Nelson K Sewankambo at Makerere University College of Health Sciences will provide oversight and support.</p><p>The study Sponsor is: Makerere University College of Health Sciences</p><p>Contact name: Prof. Nelson K Sewankambo</p><p>Address: College of Health Sciences, School of Medicine, Department of Medicine, Level 2, Clinical Research Buildi